  <description type="morphology">Leaf blades linear or linear-lanceolate, occasionally narrowly oblong-ovate or
    triangular (C. atrovirens), thick, margins entire or with pair of basal teeth or lobes, farinose
    or rarely glabrous. Inflorescences glomerules on terminal and axillary panicles. Seeds with
    margins rounded or acute; seed coat smooth, rugulate, or warty.</description>
